1
00:00:17,958 --> 00:00:19,166
♪

2
00:00:19,250 --> 00:00:21,083
[RIMURU] After we defeated
Demon Lord Geld,

3
00:00:21,166 --> 00:00:24,291
we held a meeting that included
representatives from each race.

4
00:00:24,375 --> 00:00:26,875
We needed to discuss
what would happen next.

5
00:00:26,958 --> 00:00:30,541
Well, then,
Chairman Rimuru Tempest,

6
00:00:30,625 --> 00:00:31,833
would you like to start?

7
00:00:31,916 --> 00:00:33,583
[RIMURU]
Uh...

8
00:00:33,666 --> 00:00:35,333
[chuckles]

9
00:00:35,416 --> 00:00:38,208
[RIMURU groaning nervously]

10
00:02:10,416 --> 00:02:14,541
[RIMURU] So, I've never really
done this kinda thing before.

11
00:02:14,625 --> 00:02:17,291
I'm just gonna say
what's on my mind.

12
00:02:17,375 --> 00:02:20,291
I'd like for you to reserve
your judgment until I'm done.

13
00:02:22,291 --> 00:02:23,791
First things first.

14
00:02:23,875 --> 00:02:25,291
I don't plan on
charging the orcs

15
00:02:25,375 --> 00:02:27,291
with any sort of crimes.

16
00:02:27,375 --> 00:02:29,083
[ORCS gasp]

17
00:02:30,083 --> 00:02:31,833
[RIMURU] I know this may upset
the lizardmen

18
00:02:31,916 --> 00:02:34,625
who lost the most men,
but hear me out.

19
00:02:35,791 --> 00:02:37,208
This all started
because the orcs

20
00:02:37,291 --> 00:02:39,250
were literally starving.

21
00:02:39,333 --> 00:02:41,833
Anyone of any race might have
made the same choices

22
00:02:41,916 --> 00:02:44,375
if they found themselves
in the same situation.

23
00:02:45,708 --> 00:02:48,291
Of course, that's just
my personal opinion.

24
00:02:49,708 --> 00:02:51,166
All right.

25
00:02:51,250 --> 00:02:53,250
Is there anything else
you would like to add to that?

26
00:02:54,833 --> 00:02:57,541
[RIMURU] I've taken all of
the orcs' sins upon myself.

27
00:02:57,625 --> 00:02:59,333
So direct your complaints to me.

28
00:02:59,416 --> 00:03:01,375
No. We can't allow that.

29
00:03:01,458 --> 00:03:03,166
Such a burden isn't fair to you.

30
00:03:03,250 --> 00:03:06,041
[RIMURU] Too bad.
I promised Demon Lord Geld.

31
00:03:06,125 --> 00:03:07,041
[gasps]

32
00:03:12,083 --> 00:03:14,208
I see, then.

33
00:03:14,291 --> 00:03:15,875
Still, I feel as though
your decision

34
00:03:15,958 --> 00:03:18,125
is somewhat unfair
to the rest of us.

35
00:03:18,208 --> 00:03:19,625
[RIMURU] Yeah.

36
00:03:19,708 --> 00:03:22,125
I can understand why
you wouldn't be cool with it.

37
00:03:22,208 --> 00:03:25,541
Well, there is one
undisputable rule

38
00:03:25,625 --> 00:03:26,666
all monsters follow.

39
00:03:26,750 --> 00:03:29,000
"Survival of the fittest."

40
00:03:29,083 --> 00:03:31,708
This is the way things
have always worked for our kind.

41
00:03:33,208 --> 00:03:35,916
[RIMURU] You guys lost your home
because of this mess.

42
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,500
Don't you have any complaints?

43
00:03:37,583 --> 00:03:39,916
I would be lying
if I said we didn't.

44
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:42,666
But despite them,
we will not let it happen again.

45
00:03:45,333 --> 00:03:46,625
[RIMURU]
Right.

46
00:03:46,708 --> 00:03:50,333
Very well, I suppose
you make a valid point.

47
00:03:50,416 --> 00:03:51,875
Regarding this matter,

48
00:03:51,958 --> 00:03:54,375
I do have an additional question
I'd like to ask.

49
00:03:54,458 --> 00:03:56,000
[RIMURU]
Go on.

50
00:03:56,083 --> 00:03:58,708
What do you intend to do
with the orcs?

51
00:03:59,750 --> 00:04:01,250
[sighs]

52
00:04:01,333 --> 00:04:03,250
You've already said that you
don't want to charge them

53
00:04:03,333 --> 00:04:05,250
with any crimes,
but does that also mean

54
00:04:05,333 --> 00:04:07,750
you're willing to accept
all their survivors?

55
00:04:07,833 --> 00:04:09,375
[ORCS]
Hmm.

56
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:11,875
[RIMURU]
Even after the battle,

57
00:04:11,958 --> 00:04:15,125
there are still
150,000 orcs,

58
00:04:15,208 --> 00:04:17,166
which is a lot.

59
00:04:17,250 --> 00:04:19,875
Listen, I know this might
be kind of a long shot,

60
00:04:19,958 --> 00:04:22,625
but what do you guys think
about us all working together?

61
00:04:22,708 --> 00:04:24,208
How so?

62
00:04:24,291 --> 00:04:25,500
Just what do you mean?

63
00:04:25,583 --> 00:04:26,916
[ORC A]
Hmm?

64
00:04:28,083 --> 00:04:29,375
[RIMURU]
The lizardmen will share

65
00:04:29,458 --> 00:04:31,583
their clean water source
and fish from the lake.

66
00:04:31,666 --> 00:04:33,416
The goblins can offer housing.

67
00:04:33,500 --> 00:04:37,041
And our town can provide them
with processed goods.

68
00:04:37,125 --> 00:04:38,458
And in return for those things,

69
00:04:38,541 --> 00:04:41,125
the orcs will agree
to contribute their labor.

70
00:04:41,208 --> 00:04:43,041
[ORCS gasp]

71
00:04:43,125 --> 00:04:45,416
[RIMURU] All the races
within the Great Forest of Jura

72
00:04:45,500 --> 00:04:46,875
will form an alliance

73
00:04:46,958 --> 00:04:48,958
which will be
mutually beneficial.

74
00:04:49,041 --> 00:04:50,500
Wouldn't it be cool
if we built a nation

75
00:04:50,583 --> 00:04:52,875
where all monsters
could coexist?

76
00:04:52,958 --> 00:04:56,250
Wait, but that would mean
you want us orcs

77
00:04:56,333 --> 00:04:58,666
to be a part
of your alliance, right?

78
00:04:58,750 --> 00:05:01,750
[RIMURU] No offense,
but what are your other options?

79
00:05:01,833 --> 00:05:03,916
A little labor and you've got
a place to live.

80
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:06,291
No lazy bums allowed.

81
00:05:06,375 --> 00:05:08,000
[ORCS gasp]

82
00:05:09,208 --> 00:05:10,750
[ORCS]
Right!

83
00:05:10,833 --> 00:05:12,750
[ORC A]
Of course. We'll work hard.

84
00:05:12,833 --> 00:05:15,625
In fact, we'll devote
our whole lives to helping.

85
00:05:15,708 --> 00:05:16,750
[RIMURU]
Hmm.

86
00:05:18,208 --> 00:05:19,583
[CHIEFTAIN chuckles]

87
00:05:19,666 --> 00:05:22,375
Well, then, we look forward
to working with you.

88
00:05:22,458 --> 00:05:24,500
[RIMURU] Does that sound
good to you, Treyni?

89
00:05:24,583 --> 00:05:26,875
[TREYNI]
It certainly does.

90
00:05:26,958 --> 00:05:29,416
And the dryads will offer
our protection,

91
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:32,041
as well as the bounty
of the forest.

92
00:05:32,125 --> 00:05:36,041
Which means we should be capable
of alleviating the orc's hunger.

93
00:05:36,125 --> 00:05:38,041
[ORCS gasp]

94
00:05:38,125 --> 00:05:39,375
Now...

95
00:05:40,583 --> 00:05:42,416
as caretaker of the forest,

96
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:45,041
I, Treyni,
shall make a new proclamation.

97
00:05:45,125 --> 00:05:48,166
I hereby appoint Rimuru Tempest
as the chancellor

98
00:05:48,250 --> 00:05:49,958
of the Great Forest of Jura.

99
00:05:50,041 --> 00:05:51,166
[RIMURU]
Chancellor?

100
00:05:51,250 --> 00:05:53,833
The Jura Forest Alliance
is now formed.

101
00:05:53,916 --> 00:05:57,125
Founded by Rimuru himself,
our new Chancellor.

102
00:05:58,625 --> 00:06:00,333
[RIMURU]
Wait, uh, hold on.

103
00:06:03,416 --> 00:06:06,791
Man, how the heck did I end up
as the chancellor?

104
00:06:06,875 --> 00:06:08,625
Shouldn't that be Treyni's job?

105
00:06:08,708 --> 00:06:10,875
And what's worse, it looks like

106
00:06:10,958 --> 00:06:13,125
it's too late
to try and back out.

107
00:06:13,208 --> 00:06:15,250
Fine, I guess I can do it.

108
00:06:17,958 --> 00:06:21,000
Okay, then,
as your new Slime Chancellor,

109
00:06:21,083 --> 00:06:22,833
I'm counting on all of you!

110
00:06:22,916 --> 00:06:24,250
[ALL]
Yes, sir.

111
00:06:25,375 --> 00:06:28,416
[RIMURU] There you have it,
that's how I, a humble slime,

112
00:06:28,500 --> 00:06:32,208
somehow managed to establish
the Jura Forest Alliance.

113
00:06:33,833 --> 00:06:35,083
Can I help you?

114
00:06:36,458 --> 00:06:38,791
Even if it is
"survival of the fittest,"

115
00:06:38,875 --> 00:06:42,125
hate is not an emotion
that can be forgotten so easily.

116
00:06:43,166 --> 00:06:44,541
For what we did,

117
00:06:44,625 --> 00:06:46,625
how we destroyed your village...

118
00:06:50,708 --> 00:06:53,125
I can't tell you how sorry I am.

119
00:06:53,208 --> 00:06:54,583
And I know that the request

120
00:06:54,666 --> 00:06:58,166
I'm about to make
is a selfish one, but please,

121
00:06:58,250 --> 00:07:00,291
I ask that you take my head
as penance

122
00:07:00,375 --> 00:07:01,958
and have mercy
on my people.

123
00:07:02,958 --> 00:07:05,125
[breathing heavily]

124
00:07:07,708 --> 00:07:09,791
When the battle was over,

125
00:07:09,875 --> 00:07:11,041
we told Lord Rimuru

126
00:07:11,125 --> 00:07:12,583
that we wanted
to keep serving him,

127
00:07:12,666 --> 00:07:15,208
so he gave us official titles.

128
00:07:15,291 --> 00:07:17,458
I am a Samurai,

129
00:07:17,541 --> 00:07:20,125
that's Lord Rimuru's
personal bodyguard

130
00:07:20,208 --> 00:07:21,458
and his secretary.

131
00:07:21,541 --> 00:07:24,166
[BENIMARU]
Hakurou is an instructor.

132
00:07:24,250 --> 00:07:25,708
Souei is a spy.

133
00:07:25,791 --> 00:07:29,083
The others, Shuna and Kurobe,
also have titles.

134
00:07:29,166 --> 00:07:33,375
While I have the title
of Samurai General.

135
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:38,416
I'm in charge
of military affairs.

136
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:40,750
Now that I hold
such a crucial position,

137
00:07:40,833 --> 00:07:44,125
it would be wrong of me
to rob us of a capable warrior.

138
00:07:44,208 --> 00:07:45,666
-[footsteps receding]
-Huh?

139
00:07:46,708 --> 00:07:48,750
♪

140
00:07:50,500 --> 00:07:52,333
[BENIMARU] I will show no mercy
to any of those

141
00:07:52,416 --> 00:07:53,875
who would harm Lord Rimuru.

142
00:07:53,958 --> 00:07:55,583
But if you join the alliance,

143
00:07:55,666 --> 00:07:58,333
then you and I are not enemies.

144
00:07:58,416 --> 00:08:00,375
I will never wrong him, sir.

145
00:08:00,458 --> 00:08:03,625
He is responsible
for saving my people.

146
00:08:03,708 --> 00:08:07,125
I just want to serve him,
and I'd never bear him ill will.

147
00:08:07,208 --> 00:08:08,583
[BENIMARU]
Excellent.

148
00:08:08,666 --> 00:08:11,125
That means we're fellow servants
under Lord Rimuru.

149
00:08:11,208 --> 00:08:14,583
Do your very best
to serve our master,

150
00:08:14,666 --> 00:08:16,833
and I'll accept that
as your apology.

151
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:26,000
I swear on my father
King Geld's name.

152
00:08:28,333 --> 00:08:30,666
[RIMURU] Benimaru sure is
a gracious dude.

153
00:08:30,750 --> 00:08:33,208
I could learn
something from him.

154
00:08:33,291 --> 00:08:35,916
Also, I should give
that guy a name,

155
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:38,416
since he'll be the new leader
of the orcs.

156
00:08:40,791 --> 00:08:42,458
In hopes that you inherit
the wishes

157
00:08:42,541 --> 00:08:44,625
of the late Orc Disaster
and your former king,

158
00:08:44,708 --> 00:08:46,416
I'm naming you "Geld."

159
00:08:46,500 --> 00:08:48,625
Yes, sir!

160
00:08:48,708 --> 00:08:51,291
[RIMURU] I'm trusting you
to lead the orcs well.

161
00:08:51,375 --> 00:08:52,500
Right.

162
00:08:54,708 --> 00:08:56,541
[yells]

163
00:08:58,416 --> 00:09:02,000
[RIMURU] The new orc ruler,
Geld, evolved into the Orc King.

164
00:09:03,750 --> 00:09:06,958
After that,
I spent the next ten days

165
00:09:07,041 --> 00:09:09,833
naming all 150,000 orcs.

166
00:09:12,208 --> 00:09:14,791
Obviously, that was followed up
with a mandatory nap

167
00:09:14,875 --> 00:09:16,291
due to magicule loss.

168
00:09:16,375 --> 00:09:19,250
I also decided to name
the lizardman chieftain,

169
00:09:19,333 --> 00:09:21,250
who is now known as "Abiru."

170
00:09:22,833 --> 00:09:24,166
The Chieftain's son, Gabiru,

171
00:09:24,250 --> 00:09:26,958
was charged with
the crime of treason.

172
00:09:27,041 --> 00:09:30,583
[GABIRU] I'll surely receive
the death penalty.

173
00:09:30,666 --> 00:09:32,375
It's fair.

174
00:09:32,458 --> 00:09:35,541
And the only way
to set a proper example.

175
00:09:35,625 --> 00:09:38,958
However, I do have
a single regret.

176
00:09:41,166 --> 00:09:43,125
If I could do one more thing,

177
00:09:43,208 --> 00:09:45,416
I'd ask him
why he saved my life.

178
00:09:46,458 --> 00:09:50,000
Why me?
I'm just a worthless fool.

179
00:09:50,083 --> 00:09:51,291
[ABIRU]
Raise your head.

180
00:09:53,458 --> 00:09:56,000
I'm now ready to deliver
the verdict.

181
00:09:56,083 --> 00:09:58,291
[GABIRU]
No matter what, I'm determined

182
00:09:58,375 --> 00:10:00,500
to accept the death penalty
with grace.

183
00:10:00,583 --> 00:10:04,375
For your crimes, I'm exiling you
from our clan.

184
00:10:04,458 --> 00:10:07,416
And you are forbidden to ever
call yourself a lizardman again.

185
00:10:08,458 --> 00:10:10,875
You are to leave here
immediately.

186
00:10:10,958 --> 00:10:13,625
[GABIRU]
Wait. Seriously?!

187
00:10:17,166 --> 00:10:18,000
[GABIRU grunts]

188
00:10:19,250 --> 00:10:22,375
You forgot this. Take it.

189
00:10:22,458 --> 00:10:23,500
[GABIRU gasps]

190
00:10:25,250 --> 00:10:27,666
♪

191
00:10:42,208 --> 00:10:45,000
[LIZARDMAN 2 laughs]
Sir Gabiru!

192
00:10:45,083 --> 00:10:47,041
-Sir Gabiru!
-Hey!

193
00:10:48,125 --> 00:10:49,833
Thank goodness,
we've been waiting for you.

194
00:10:49,916 --> 00:10:51,458
Yeah.
What took you so long?

195
00:10:51,541 --> 00:10:53,125
We were starting to worry.

196
00:10:53,208 --> 00:10:56,458
Uh, I'm not even sure
why you're here.

197
00:10:56,541 --> 00:10:58,250
You must be aware I was exiled.

198
00:10:58,333 --> 00:11:01,333
Well, sure, but if
you're exiled, then we are, too.

199
00:11:01,416 --> 00:11:02,458
That is true.

200
00:11:03,708 --> 00:11:04,875
[voice breaking]
You guys...

201
00:11:06,541 --> 00:11:08,250
are all idiots!

202
00:11:10,375 --> 00:11:11,625
[GABIRU sniffles]

203
00:11:11,708 --> 00:11:14,625
Not to mention
you're completely hopeless!

204
00:11:14,708 --> 00:11:18,250
Fine then, I guess I'll just
have to look after you.

205
00:11:18,333 --> 00:11:21,041
Follow me, men,
to a brighter future!

206
00:11:21,125 --> 00:11:22,625
Whew. Sounds good.

207
00:11:22,708 --> 00:11:25,416
-Hooray! [laughs]
-Let's go!

208
00:11:28,583 --> 00:11:31,000
[LAPLACE] After all the trouble
you went to set that up,

209
00:11:31,083 --> 00:11:32,583
it must drive you bonkers

210
00:11:32,666 --> 00:11:34,833
that a new Demon Lord
wasn't born.

211
00:11:34,916 --> 00:11:36,791
[MAN]
Perhaps a little.

212
00:11:38,750 --> 00:11:42,333
Still though,
it was an amazing spectacle.

213
00:11:42,416 --> 00:11:45,875
And that Slime,
what shall I do with it?

214
00:11:45,958 --> 00:11:48,541
[LAPLACE] Sounds like you have
plans to make.

215
00:11:48,625 --> 00:11:50,958
Well, should you
ever need a hand,

216
00:11:51,041 --> 00:11:54,166
I'll lend you one for cheap,
Demon Lord Clayman.

217
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:58,041
[chuckles]

218
00:12:00,833 --> 00:12:03,416
[RIMURU] Three months after
the downfall of the Orc Lord,

219
00:12:03,500 --> 00:12:05,708
the orcs, who had
evolved into high orcs,

220
00:12:05,791 --> 00:12:07,125
were thriving under Kaijin

221
00:12:07,208 --> 00:12:09,666
and the other dwarves'
expert tutelage.

222
00:12:09,750 --> 00:12:12,208
They were now valuable members
of the community.

223
00:12:15,291 --> 00:12:18,208
[RIMURU] Mm-hmm! The houses
are turning out nicely.

224
00:12:18,291 --> 00:12:20,333
Everyone has clothes and tools.

225
00:12:20,416 --> 00:12:24,000
But the best part is,
our bangin' aqueduct!

226
00:12:24,083 --> 00:12:27,041
We've got flushing toilets,
clean water and sewage systems!

227
00:12:27,125 --> 00:12:29,083
We're even building roads.

228
00:12:29,166 --> 00:12:31,000
Guess my years
in general contracting

229
00:12:31,083 --> 00:12:32,083
have paid off.

230
00:12:32,166 --> 00:12:33,375
These roads will be awesome

231
00:12:33,458 --> 00:12:35,083
when we start doing
commerce and stuff.

232
00:12:35,166 --> 00:12:38,208
And the bath I requested
is almost finished.

233
00:12:38,291 --> 00:12:40,083
Oh, man, I can't wait!

234
00:12:40,166 --> 00:12:42,000
Pretty cool, huh, Ranga?

235
00:12:42,083 --> 00:12:44,083
Everyone has worked together
and now our little village

236
00:12:44,166 --> 00:12:46,583
is a thriving haven
for monsters everywhere.

237
00:12:46,666 --> 00:12:50,041
[RANGA] Yes.
It is truly magnificent, master.

238
00:12:50,125 --> 00:12:51,375
[RIMURU]
Mm-hmm.

239
00:12:52,750 --> 00:12:54,791
Our town was almost finished.

240
00:12:54,875 --> 00:12:57,583
Soon we'd have a peaceful place
to call home.

241
00:12:58,791 --> 00:13:02,125
Of course life rarely goes
the way we plan.

242
00:13:03,625 --> 00:13:06,083
Lord Rimuru,
there's an emergency.

243
00:13:06,166 --> 00:13:07,333
[RIMURU]
Huh?

244
00:13:10,583 --> 00:13:12,708
♪

245
00:13:16,416 --> 00:13:18,708
[SOUEI] The sky is filled
with Pegasus Knights,

246
00:13:18,791 --> 00:13:20,250
and they're heading our way.

247
00:13:20,333 --> 00:13:21,375
[RIMURU]
What?

248
00:13:21,458 --> 00:13:23,166
♪

249
00:13:26,083 --> 00:13:27,791
Hmm.

250
00:13:31,083 --> 00:13:33,791
My King,
what did the letter say?

251
00:13:33,875 --> 00:13:35,833
[GAZEL]
The Orc Lord was defeated.

252
00:13:35,916 --> 00:13:39,083
It seems the war has ended.

253
00:13:39,166 --> 00:13:40,708
It's over?

254
00:13:40,791 --> 00:13:43,333
The remaining 150,000 orcs

255
00:13:43,416 --> 00:13:46,083
surrendered their arms
and have now scattered.

256
00:13:46,166 --> 00:13:48,708
What's more, they've all
evolved into high orcs.

257
00:13:48,791 --> 00:13:50,291
That can't be.

258
00:13:52,208 --> 00:13:54,583
[GAZEL] The message reported
that several superior majin

259
00:13:54,666 --> 00:13:56,125
participated in the battle.

260
00:13:56,208 --> 00:13:57,791
It might be presumptuous of me,

261
00:13:57,875 --> 00:14:01,041
but I assume they are
all serving that Slime.

262
00:14:02,250 --> 00:14:06,666
A Slime capable of ruling majin
and causing monsters to evolve.

263
00:14:06,750 --> 00:14:08,333
How troublesome.

264
00:14:08,416 --> 00:14:10,625
If this matter
is not handled with care,

265
00:14:10,708 --> 00:14:12,041
then the nation may fall.

266
00:14:16,458 --> 00:14:18,333
I will go visit this Slime.

267
00:14:18,416 --> 00:14:21,916
If nothing else, I would like to
appraise it's worth myself.

268
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:25,500
♪

269
00:14:36,125 --> 00:14:37,375
[panting]

270
00:14:45,875 --> 00:14:46,750
[SHION gasps]

271
00:14:49,791 --> 00:14:52,208
Hmm. It's him.

272
00:14:52,291 --> 00:14:55,125
[RIMURU]
The hero king of the dwarves.

273
00:14:55,208 --> 00:14:57,166
Gazel Dwargo.

274
00:14:57,250 --> 00:15:00,625
Well, Lord Rimuru,
what should we do?

275
00:15:00,708 --> 00:15:02,916
[RIMURU] I'd like to avoid
a fight, if possible.

276
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:04,375
No worries, my lord.

277
00:15:04,458 --> 00:15:06,041
You want me to destroy them?

278
00:15:06,125 --> 00:15:08,125
[RIMURU sighs]

279
00:15:08,208 --> 00:15:11,125
[RIMURU] If this goes south,
I want you to evacuate the town.

280
00:15:11,208 --> 00:15:13,708
We can buy time
while everyone else escapes.

281
00:15:13,791 --> 00:15:15,541
Right.

282
00:15:18,041 --> 00:15:19,750
[KAIJIN panting]

283
00:15:22,791 --> 00:15:24,833
It's good to see you,
Your Majesty.

284
00:15:26,375 --> 00:15:28,583
Have you been
doing well, Kaijin?

285
00:15:28,666 --> 00:15:29,958
Yes.

286
00:15:32,958 --> 00:15:35,208
The Slime.

287
00:15:35,291 --> 00:15:37,500
[RIMURU]
Allow me to introduce myself.

288
00:15:37,583 --> 00:15:39,041
My name's Rimuru.

289
00:15:39,125 --> 00:15:41,958
While I am a slime, I'd rather
you didn't call me that.

290
00:15:42,041 --> 00:15:46,041
Because I'm also the chancellor
of the Jura Forest Alliance.

291
00:15:47,833 --> 00:15:50,250
Obviously this isn't
my actual form,

292
00:15:50,333 --> 00:15:52,708
but it should at least
make talking easier.

293
00:15:52,791 --> 00:15:55,250
So, what can I do for you?

294
00:15:55,333 --> 00:15:57,125
I'll get straight to the point.

295
00:15:57,208 --> 00:16:01,125
You see, I'm here to determine
your worth.

296
00:16:01,208 --> 00:16:02,916
Meaning?

297
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:05,125
[GAZEL]
I'll judge you.

298
00:16:05,208 --> 00:16:07,500
Using nothing
but the steel of my weapon.

299
00:16:07,583 --> 00:16:08,750
[RIMURU gasps]

300
00:16:08,833 --> 00:16:10,958
[GAZEL]
If you insist on boasting

301
00:16:11,041 --> 00:16:13,250
about being
chancellor of this forest,

302
00:16:13,333 --> 00:16:16,500
then it's up to me and my sword
to put you in your place.

303
00:16:16,583 --> 00:16:20,083
Unless that toy on your hip
is just a decoration,

304
00:16:20,166 --> 00:16:22,875
you had better
accept my challenge.

305
00:16:24,166 --> 00:16:25,833
Please, sir, don't do this.

306
00:16:25,916 --> 00:16:27,125
[scoffs]

307
00:16:27,208 --> 00:16:29,208
Would a fight not be
the most direct way

308
00:16:29,291 --> 00:16:30,833
to settle this dispute?

309
00:16:30,916 --> 00:16:34,375
All right.
Have it your way, then.

310
00:16:34,458 --> 00:16:36,791
But I'll make you regret
accusing me of bragging.

311
00:16:38,833 --> 00:16:41,166
♪

312
00:16:50,958 --> 00:16:52,041
[GAZEL]
If you can defend

313
00:16:52,125 --> 00:16:53,750
against my entire chain
of attacks,

314
00:16:53,833 --> 00:16:55,500
I'll declare you the winner.

315
00:16:55,583 --> 00:16:57,000
[RIMURU gasps]

316
00:16:57,083 --> 00:16:59,208
[GAZEL]
However, I should warn you

317
00:16:59,291 --> 00:17:01,208
that in addition
to being a king,

318
00:17:01,291 --> 00:17:03,750
I am also a master swordsman.

319
00:17:03,833 --> 00:17:05,250
Got it.

320
00:17:05,333 --> 00:17:07,375
[wind whooshing]

321
00:17:09,333 --> 00:17:12,750
Very well. Then I shall serve
as witness to this contest.

322
00:17:14,291 --> 00:17:16,750
It can't be. A dryad?

323
00:17:18,291 --> 00:17:19,875
[GAZEL chuckles]

324
00:17:19,958 --> 00:17:23,000
I suppose I should apologize
for accusing you of boasting.

325
00:17:23,083 --> 00:17:24,916
I think I have
a better understanding

326
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:26,500
of what's going on now.

327
00:17:26,583 --> 00:17:27,708
Yeah?

328
00:17:27,791 --> 00:17:29,208
But regardless of that,

329
00:17:29,291 --> 00:17:31,666
I still need to evaluate
your true nature.

330
00:17:31,750 --> 00:17:33,125
Aww.

331
00:17:34,333 --> 00:17:36,208
Now that we have a witness
for our battle,

332
00:17:36,291 --> 00:17:38,666
you and I are ready
to cross swords.

333
00:17:38,750 --> 00:17:41,375
Fine then, bring it on.

334
00:17:41,458 --> 00:17:43,583
But after I win,
you'd better be prepared

335
00:17:43,666 --> 00:17:45,458
to explain your real reason
for coming here.

336
00:17:45,541 --> 00:17:47,208
[laughs]

337
00:17:47,291 --> 00:17:49,750
If you somehow do,
I'll give you an answer.

338
00:17:51,375 --> 00:17:52,208
Begin.

339
00:17:52,291 --> 00:17:54,875
♪

340
00:18:03,458 --> 00:18:06,875
And here I thought you'd be
more powerful, Rimuru.

341
00:18:06,958 --> 00:18:08,458
Bite me.

342
00:18:08,541 --> 00:18:11,166
Wait until I start taking
this seriously, King Gazel.

343
00:18:13,291 --> 00:18:14,625
[yelling]

344
00:18:18,958 --> 00:18:21,750
[RIMURU]
Man, he really is a beast.

345
00:18:21,833 --> 00:18:24,541
But I can't exactly afford
to lose this contest.

346
00:18:24,625 --> 00:18:26,291
[scoffs]

347
00:18:28,458 --> 00:18:29,666
[RIMURU]
Wait, that stance.

348
00:18:29,750 --> 00:18:31,625
Here I come, Rimuru.

349
00:18:31,708 --> 00:18:33,875
Haze: Thunder of Heaven
and Earth!

350
00:18:34,916 --> 00:18:36,166
[gasps]

351
00:18:38,166 --> 00:18:40,000
[RIMURU]
The next strike is above!

352
00:18:48,041 --> 00:18:49,791
[grunting]

353
00:18:51,458 --> 00:18:52,666
[GAZEL]
Hmm.

354
00:18:52,750 --> 00:18:54,125
[chuckles]

355
00:18:54,208 --> 00:18:55,375
[laughs]

356
00:18:55,458 --> 00:18:57,458
I can't believe
you blocked my attack.

357
00:18:57,541 --> 00:18:58,750
Huh?

358
00:18:58,833 --> 00:19:00,500
Enough.

359
00:19:00,583 --> 00:19:03,041
The winner is Rimuru Tempest.

360
00:19:04,416 --> 00:19:05,541
Uh...

361
00:19:06,833 --> 00:19:09,291
Now that we've battled,
I know the truth.

362
00:19:09,375 --> 00:19:11,750
It's obvious that you are not
a malicious being.

363
00:19:11,833 --> 00:19:13,000
-[ALL] Mm-hmm.
-[RIMURU sighs]

364
00:19:13,083 --> 00:19:14,750
No flipping duh.

365
00:19:14,833 --> 00:19:16,208
I have to admit it,

366
00:19:16,291 --> 00:19:18,125
I'm impressed that you
saw through my Haze:

367
00:19:18,208 --> 00:19:20,458
Thunder of Heaven
and Earth attack.

368
00:19:20,541 --> 00:19:22,791
You're an excellent fighter,
Rimuru.

369
00:19:22,875 --> 00:19:24,833
It was more luck than anything.

370
00:19:24,916 --> 00:19:27,041
It just so happens
my master uses that move

371
00:19:27,125 --> 00:19:29,125
all the time in training,
so I'm used to it.

372
00:19:29,208 --> 00:19:30,541
Pretty crazy, huh?

373
00:19:30,625 --> 00:19:32,000
He does?

374
00:19:32,083 --> 00:19:34,750
Hold on.
Who did you say your master was?

375
00:19:34,833 --> 00:19:35,833
[gasps]

376
00:19:36,833 --> 00:19:38,208
[laughs]

377
00:19:38,291 --> 00:19:40,791
That was excellent work,
Lord Rimuru.

378
00:19:40,875 --> 00:19:43,541
You're the Savant.

379
00:19:43,625 --> 00:19:45,750
You don't look anything
like the little boy

380
00:19:45,833 --> 00:19:48,666
I found lost in the forest,
you're much bigger now.

381
00:19:48,750 --> 00:19:51,208
Oh. Do forgive me, King Gazel.

382
00:19:51,291 --> 00:19:52,875
I have to admit I'm overjoyed

383
00:19:52,958 --> 00:19:55,625
to see that you have surpassed
my own skill with the sword.

384
00:19:55,708 --> 00:19:58,666
It's an honor to receive
such a huge compliment.

385
00:19:58,750 --> 00:20:01,166
[RIMURU]
Hakurou was his master?

386
00:20:01,250 --> 00:20:03,708
I'm pretty surprised at how
connected everyone can be,

387
00:20:03,791 --> 00:20:05,583
even in a world like this one.

388
00:20:05,666 --> 00:20:07,958
-[indistinct conversations]
-[laughter]

389
00:20:12,791 --> 00:20:15,541
I see.
This was about the Orc Lord.

390
00:20:15,625 --> 00:20:18,083
You wanted to know
who was behind his downfall.

391
00:20:18,166 --> 00:20:21,416
Yes, and to see whether
they were friends or enemies.

392
00:20:21,500 --> 00:20:22,875
Now you understand.

393
00:20:24,958 --> 00:20:27,333
Rimuru, may I ask something?

394
00:20:27,416 --> 00:20:28,875
Sure.

395
00:20:28,958 --> 00:20:32,583
Would you be interested
in entering a treaty with me?

396
00:20:32,666 --> 00:20:33,625
Huh?

397
00:20:34,833 --> 00:20:36,333
[GAZEL]
If you were to gain control

398
00:20:36,416 --> 00:20:39,916
of everything in this forest
and its surrounding areas,

399
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:42,625
it's possible you could obtain
wealth and power surpassing

400
00:20:42,708 --> 00:20:44,416
that of my own nation.

401
00:20:44,500 --> 00:20:45,791
And that's why,

402
00:20:45,875 --> 00:20:47,708
it's imperative
that you gain support

403
00:20:47,791 --> 00:20:49,125
from another country.

404
00:20:49,208 --> 00:20:51,458
Don't get me wrong,
that'd be awesome, but...

405
00:20:54,333 --> 00:20:55,708
It's just...

406
00:20:55,791 --> 00:20:57,291
Are you really okay
with acknowledging

407
00:20:57,375 --> 00:20:59,875
our monster town
as its own nation?

408
00:20:59,958 --> 00:21:01,875
That's a pretty big deal,
you know?

409
00:21:01,958 --> 00:21:05,500
I do, and I accept it.

410
00:21:05,583 --> 00:21:07,625
This deal would benefit
both our parties.

411
00:21:07,708 --> 00:21:09,833
In this event,
we all stand to profit.

412
00:21:09,916 --> 00:21:10,791
[RIMURU sighs]

413
00:21:12,375 --> 00:21:14,333
Not like I can really refuse.

414
00:21:15,750 --> 00:21:17,250
Right, consider it a deal.

415
00:21:17,333 --> 00:21:18,958
Thank you.

416
00:21:19,041 --> 00:21:22,250
So, all that's left is for you
to pick a name for your nation.

417
00:21:22,333 --> 00:21:24,291
[gasps]

418
00:21:24,375 --> 00:21:26,208
[RIMURU]
Cool, I'm just naming a nation.

419
00:21:26,291 --> 00:21:28,583
No pressure or anything!

420
00:21:28,666 --> 00:21:30,041
Let's see.

421
00:21:30,125 --> 00:21:32,166
Maybe I can combine
the "Forest of Jura"

422
00:21:32,250 --> 00:21:34,791
and "Rimuru Tempest" somehow.

423
00:21:34,875 --> 00:21:37,541
It's the
Jura Tempest Federation.

424
00:21:37,625 --> 00:21:40,291
Ah, that's an excellent choice
for a name.

425
00:21:40,375 --> 00:21:43,041
-[BENIMARU chuckles]
-That's our Lord Rimuru.

426
00:21:43,125 --> 00:21:44,250
Hold on.

427
00:21:44,333 --> 00:21:46,666
If this is the
Jura Tempest Federation,

428
00:21:46,750 --> 00:21:49,583
then we have to name our town
Rimuru after our lord.

429
00:21:49,666 --> 00:21:50,833
[gasps]

430
00:21:50,916 --> 00:21:52,833
It'll be the nation's capital.

431
00:21:52,916 --> 00:21:53,750
[RIMURU]
Hang on.

432
00:21:53,833 --> 00:21:55,125
That's kinda embarrassi--

433
00:21:55,208 --> 00:21:58,041
What a fantastic idea.
No other name would do.

434
00:21:58,125 --> 00:21:59,458
Right, I agree.

435
00:21:59,541 --> 00:22:01,375
No one here could possibly
object to that name.

436
00:22:01,458 --> 00:22:03,250
[RIMURU]
Except me.

437
00:22:03,333 --> 00:22:05,000
It sounds like it's settled.

438
00:22:07,250 --> 00:22:08,208
[RIMURU]
Yeah.

439
00:22:10,666 --> 00:22:13,041
In that moment,
A new nation was born,

440
00:22:13,125 --> 00:22:15,291
and the names
"Jura Tempest Federation"

441
00:22:15,375 --> 00:22:16,833
and "Capital City Rimuru"

442
00:22:16,916 --> 00:22:19,750
were engraved into history
for the first time.

443
00:23:52,958 --> 00:23:56,000
[GREAT SAGE] Next time,
"Demon Lord Milim Attacks."

